data.text: It might not have the most inspiring name in the world, but don’t be fooled — a visit to the Manchester Museum is a deep dive into a rabbit hole of archeology, anthropology and natural history covering every single continent on the planet. There are literally millions of artefacts here, all housed in a stunning building on Oxford Road. We’re always interested in taxidermy, that much should be clear by now.
